message:
make classes implement Handler.Callback instead of making local Handler

Many classes used an anonymous Handler class stored in a class variable
for handling message callbacks:

	Handler handle = new Handler() { ... }

Instead, the class should implement Handler.Callback which requires adding
boolean handleMessage(Message) and create the handle variable with:

	Handler handle = new Handler(this);

return early in ManualPanel.onMeasure if no children views

if there are no views within the ManualPanel just call:
	setMeasuredDimension(maxWidth, maxHeight);

add FileLogger to log exceptions to a file (add NetworkClient logging)

Some app markets provide stack traces of crashes, but many times this
is not enough information. The FileLogger takes an exception stack trace
and optionally a set of Object variables with an associated name. These
are then printed out to a file with a timestamp. For example

FileLogger log = new FileLogger(new Exception("something bad!"));
log.addItem("myVar", myVar);
log.write();

Currently only exceptions in NetworkClient have been added to the logger.

update GameListOnline's PageAdapter to not use deprecated api

The following functions are deprecated:

public Object instantiateItem (View container, int position)
public void destroyItem (View container, int position, Object object)
public void finishUpdate (View container)
public void startUpdate (View container)

Use the updated functions instead:

public Object instantiateItem (ViewGroup container, int position)
public void destroyItem (ViewGroup container, int position, Object object)
public void finishUpdate (ViewGroup container)
public void startUpdate (ViewGroup container)

add new server commands to NetworkClient to get/set options

The server now supports user options to be saved and queried.
The two new functions added to NetworkClient are:

public <Type> void set_option(final String option, final Type value)
public void get_option(final String option)
